Exaplanation: 

We created seperate header and source files for our class which resulted in this header file.

ifndef stands for "if not defined". The first of statement tells the program to define the MyCLass header file if it hasnt been defined already. "endif" ends the condition



Example:

#ifndef MYCLASS_H
#define MYCLASS_H

class MyClass
{
  public:
  MyClass();
  protected:
  private:
};

#endif // MYCLASS_H 

REASON:
this prevents from the header being included more than once in the file.

Follow Up Question:
What is the purpose of #ifndef #define directives in header files?

Answer:
They prevent a header file from being included more than once within one file